City of Waycross et al. v. Ballard et al. No. 3783. February 27, 1924. • Parker & Parker and Parks, Peed & Garrett, for plaintiffs in error. Wilson & Bennett and S. F. Memory, contra.

This case came before this court on a writ of error from the superior court of Ware County, and being for decision by a full bench of six Justices, who are equally divided in opinion, Atkinson, Gilbert and Hines, JJ., being for affirmance, and Russell, C. J., Beck, P. J., and Hill, J., being for reversal of the court below, the case stands affirmed by operation of law.

Injunction. Before Judge Summerall. Ware superior court. April 19, 1923.
